# AsliJobs Frontend Design System

## Typography Standard

- Use ONLY the Inter font family throughout the AsliJobs project.
- Never introduce another font family unless explicitly approved.
- All future pages, components, forms, dialogs, dashboards, landing pages, employer pages, admin pages, and mobile layouts must inherit Inter from the global design system.
- Do not import fonts locally inside components.
- Always use the global Inter font configured in the root layout (`src/app/layout.tsx`).
- Official typography constants live in `src/constants/design-system.ts`.
- Global CSS maps `--font-sans` to `--font-inter` in `src/app/globals.css`.

## Typography Rules for New Work

- Do not add `next/font` imports in feature components, pages, or layouts other than the root layout.
- Do not hardcode `font-family` values that override Inter.
- Prefer the existing `font-sans` utility and inherited body styles.
- Keep font sizes, font weights, line heights, and letter spacing as defined by existing component classes — only the typeface family is Inter.

## Scope

This rule applies to every frontend surface, including:

- Landing page and hero
- Navbar and footer
- Search bar
- Resources
- Employer pages
- Post Job flow
- Authentication pages
- Dashboards
- Dialogs, modals, forms, cards, tables
- All future pages and features
